Commentary Text: Shahbaz Ahmed to Hooda, out Caught by Rajat Patidar!! Walks straight into the trap! With the leg-side boundary being bigger at this end, the ploy was for Shahbaz to attack the middle-and-leg line and force the big shot across the line. Hooda tries to go over fine leg with his swivel-sweep but doesn't quite connect well. Top edges it high towards the long leg region where Padikkal moves forward to settle under it. Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Kohli, out Bowled!! This partnership was going nowhere, so Kohli, literally, decides to go down the pitch, on a rather aimless walk. Commentary Text: Riley Meredith to Devdutt Padikkal, out Bowled!! Meredith has destroyed the off stump here! He had been clocking high speeds from ball one, so it was probably the wrong call from Padikkal to charge at the Aussie. Could have instead used that pace to find the big gaps available in the powerplay. But the fire of youth means that Padikkal does come down the track and makes room for the big shot but this is just too quick for him. Flattens the off pole and Kohli is livid at the non-striker's end. Probably he too felt that it was bad shot selection. Meredith is pumping his fist in excitement. Much-needed early strike for Punjab. Devdutt Padikkal b Riley Meredith 7(6) [6s-1]
